  "text": "Direct comparison in competitive transplant models showed that short-term exposure of HSCs to PGE 2 produces an approximately 4-fold competitive advantage, consistent with published results. [CITATION_1] However, previous studies showed a maximal effect on HSC frequency at 12 weeks after transplantation with reduced HSC frequency at 24 weeks, suggesting a greater effect on short-term rather than long-term repopulating cells. Our studies show that PGE 2 -induced enhancement of HSC frequency was stable throughout a more than 20-week period and was maintained in secondary transplantations through 24 weeks, clearly indicating a sustained effect on LTRC. The reasons for this difference in repopulating stability are not clear, but may relate to more precise head-to-head quantitation of HSC competition in our model.",
